bytecode

Class CAST

  • java.lang.Object
    • bytecode.Bytecode

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NonCallingBytecode

    public class CAST
extends NonCallingSequentialBytecode
    A bytecode that casts the top of the stack into a given type. If the cast is not possible, the program stops. A reference value can only be cast towards its type or a subtype of its type. In that case, the cast value is original value, unmodified. The value nil can be cast towards any reference type and remains unmodified. A numerical type can be cast into any numerical type through a type conversion. No other casts are possible.

    ..., value -> ..., cast value
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto
